Notice that $a + b = 4c$. Cubing both sides gives \[a^3 + b^3 + 3ab(a + b) = 64c^3.\]By substitution, \[15x - 1 + 13x + 1 + 3(15x - 1)^{1/3}(13x + 1)^{1/3}(4\sqrt[3]{x}) = 64x.\]Simplify the left-hand side and factor an $x$ out of all three terms: \[28x + (720x^2 - 12x)^{1/3} = 64x.\]Next, isolate the cube root and cube both sides again to get \[720x^2 - 12x = 2744x^3 - 3088x^2 + 12x.\]Simplify and factor an $x$ out to get \[28x^2(97x - 41) = 0.\]Hence, $x = 0$ and $x = \frac{41}{97}.$</think> 0, \frac{41}{97}
